hopobject.body: We went to university together medicalartshospital.org "People should know enough about their animal when they get it and after they get it," Hendricks says. "They also must be open to the idea that they may not know as much as they thought." Even dog breeds vary in terms of what they need from people, Hendricks says. Some dogs are meant to work, some need intellectual stimulation and some need little exercise. Bulldogs, for instance, are happy to lie at home sleeping a lot and show affection when you return from work. Great Danes also don't need to run around much.
